p.font: // goroutine 使用的数据结构
type g struct {
// 栈参数
// stack 描述当前 goroutine 的栈内存实际范围：[stack.lo, stack.hi)
// stackguard0 is the stack pointer compared in the Go stack growth prologue.
// It is stack.lo+StackGuard normally, but can be StackPreempt to trigger a preemption.
// stackguard1 is the stack pointer compared in the C stack growth prologue.
// It is stack.lo+StackGuard on g0 and gsignal stacks.
// It is ~0 on other goroutine stacks, to trigger a call to morestackc (and crash).
stack stack // offset known to runtime/cgo
stackguard0 uintptr // 该字段被设置为 StackPreempt 意味着当前 Goroutine 发出了抢占请求
stackguard1 uintptr // offset known to liblink
_panic *_panic // 最内侧的 panic 结构体
_defer *_defer // 最内侧的延迟函数结构体
m *m // 当前 goroutine 占用的线程，可能为空
sched gobuf // 存储 goroutine 的调度相关的数据
syscallsp uintptr // if status==Gsyscall, syscallsp = sched.sp to use during gc
syscallpc uintptr // if status==Gsyscall, syscallpc = sched.pc to use during gc
stktopsp uintptr // expected sp at top of stack, to check in traceback
param unsafe.Pointer // 唤醒时传递的参数
atomicstatus uint32 // goroutine 的状态
stackLock uint32 // sigprof/scang lock; TODO: fold in to atomicstatus
goid int64 // goroutine 的 ID，不公开
schedlink guintptr
waitsince int64 // approx time when the g become blocked
waitreason waitReason // goroutine 处于 Gwaiting 状态时的等待原因
preempt bool // 抢占信号，duplicates stackguard0 = stackpreempt
preemptStop bool // 抢占时将状态修改成 _Gpreempted；otherwise, just deschedule
preemptShrink bool // 在同步安全点收缩栈
// 如果 goroutine 停在异步安全点的时候会设置 asyncSafePoint
// 这表示栈中存在没有确切指针信息的帧。
asyncSafePoint bool
paniconfault bool // panic (instead of crash) on unexpected fault address
gcscandone bool // g has scanned stack; protected by _Gscan bit in status
throwsplit bool // must not split stack
// activeStackChans indicates that there are unlocked channels
// pointing into this goroutine's stack. If true, stack
// copying needs to acquire channel locks to protect these
// areas of the stack.
activeStackChans bool
raceignore int8 // 忽略竞争检测事件
sysblocktraced bool // StartTrace has emitted EvGoInSyscall about this goroutine
sysexitticks int64 // cputicks when syscall has returned (for tracing)
traceseq uint64 // trace event sequencer
tracelastp puintptr // last P emitted an event for this goroutine
lockedm muintptr
sig uint32
writebuf []byte
sigcode0 uintptr
sigcode1 uintptr
sigpc uintptr
gopc uintptr // pc of go statement that created this goroutine
ancestors *[]ancestorInfo // ancestor information goroutine(s) that created this goroutine (only used if debug.tracebackancestors)
startpc uintptr // goroutine 函数(fn)的 pc 值
racectx uintptr
waiting *sudog // sudog structures this g is waiting on (that have a valid elem ptr); in lock order
cgoCtxt []uintptr // cgo traceback context
labels unsafe.Pointer // profiler labels
timer *timer // cached timer for time.Sleep
selectDone uint32 // are we participating in a select and did someone win the race?
// Per-G GC state
// gcAssistBytes is this G's GC assist credit in terms of
// bytes allocated. If this is positive, then the G has credit
// to allocate gcAssistBytes bytes without assisting. If this
// is negative, then the G must correct this by performing
// scan work. We track this in bytes to make it fast to update
// and check for debt in the malloc hot path. The assist ratio
// determines how this corresponds to scan work debt.
gcAssistBytes int64

p.font: type gobuf struct {
// The offsets of sp, pc, and g are known to (hard-coded in) libmach.
// ctxt is unusual with respect to GC: it may be a
p.span: heap-allocated funcval, so GC needs to track it, but it
needs to be set and cleared from assembly, where it's
difficult to have write barriers. However, ctxt is really a
saved, live register, and we only ever exchange it between
the real register and the gobuf. Hence, we treat it as a
root during stack scanning, which means assembly that saves
and restores it doesn't need write barriers. It's still
typed as a pointer so that any other writes from Go get
write barriers.

p.font: sp uintptr // 栈指针
pc uintptr // 程序计数器
g guintptr // 持有 runtime.gobuf 的 goroutine
ctxt unsafe.Pointer
ret sys.Uintreg // 函数调用的返回值
// 上面这几个字段会在调度器保存或者恢复上下文的时候用到，其中，栈指针和程序计数器被用来存储或者恢复寄存器中的值，改变程序即将执行的代码。
lr uintptr
bp uintptr // for GOEXPERIMENT=framepointer

p.font: const (
// runtime.runtime2.go
// 除了表示 goroutine 的常规状态，它还像是 goroutine 栈空间（以及执行用户代码的能力）上的锁。
// _Gidle 表示这个 goroutine 刚被分配，并且还没有被初始化
_Gidle = iota // 0
// _Grunnable 表示这个 goroutine 存储在运行队列中，当前尚未执行用户代码，没有栈的所有权
_Grunnable // 1
// _Grunning 表示这个 goroutine 可以执行用户代码，拥有栈的所有权。
// 它不在运行队列中，被赋予了内核线程 M 和处理器 P（g.m 和 g.m.p 现在是有效的）
_Grunning // 2
// _Gsyscall 表示这个 goroutine 正在执行一个系统调用，拥有栈的所有权，没有执行用户代码
// 它被赋予了内核线程，但不在运行队列中。
_Gsyscall // 3
// _Gwaiting 表示这个 goroutine 因为运行时而阻塞。它没有执行用户代码，并且不在运行队列中
// but should be recorded somewhere (e.g., a channel wait
p.span: queue) so it can be ready()d when necessary. The stack is
not owned *except* that a channel operation may read or
write parts of the stack under the appropriate channel
lock. Otherwise, it is not safe to access the stack after a
goroutine enters _Gwaiting (e.g., it may get moved).

p.font: _Gwaiting // 4
// _Gmoribund_unused 当前已不再使用
_Gmoribund_unused // 5
// _Gdead 意味着这个 goroutine 当前没有被使用。It may be
p.span: just exited, on a free list, or just being initialized. It
is not executing user code. It may or may not have a stack
allocated. The G and its stack (if any) are owned by the M
that is exiting the G or that obtained the G from the free
list.

p.font: _Gdead // 6
// _Genqueue_unused 当前已不再使用
_Genqueue_unused // 7
// _Gcopystack 意味着这个 goroutine 的栈正在被移动。它没有执行用户代码也不在运行队列上
// 栈属于将其放在 _Gcopystack 上的那个 goroutine
_Gcopystack // 8
// _Gpreempted 意味着这个 goroutine 由于 suspendG 抢占而停止。
// 像 _Gwaiting，但是，nothing is
// yet responsible for ready()ing it. Some suspendG must CAS
// the status to _Gwaiting to take responsibility for
// ready()ing this G.
_Gpreempted // 9
// _Gscan 与上面其中一个状态（除了_Grunning）组合在一起，表示
p.span: GC 正在扫描栈空间。

p.font: // 这个 goroutine 没有执行用户代码，并且栈的所有权属于设置 _Gscan 的那个 goroutine。
// _Gscanrunning 不同：it is used to briefly block
p.span: state transitions while GC signals the G to scan its own
stack. This is otherwise like _Grunning.

p.font: // atomicstatus&~Gscan gives the state the goroutine will
p.span: return to when the scan completes.

p.font: _Gscan = 0x1000
_Gscanrunnable = _Gscan + _Grunnable // 0x1001
_Gscanrunning = _Gscan + _Grunning // 0x1002
_Gscansyscall = _Gscan + _Gsyscall // 0x1003
_Gscanwaiting = _Gscan + _Gwaiting // 0x1004
_Gscanpreempted = _Gscan + _Gpreempted // 0x1009

p.font: // 表示操作系统线程的数据结构
type m struct {
g0 *g // 持有调度栈的 goroutine
morebuf gobuf // gobuf arg to morestack
divmod uint32 // div/mod denominator for arm - known to liblink
// Fields not known to debuggers.
procid uint64 // for debuggers, but offset not hard-coded
gsignal *g // signal-handling g
goSigStack gsignalStack // Go-allocated signal handling stack
sigmask sigset // storage for saved signal mask
tls [6]uintptr // thread-local storage (for x86 extern register)
mstartfn func()
curg *g // 当前线程上运行中的 goroutine
caughtsig guintptr // goroutine running during fatal signal
p puintptr // 正在运行代码的处理器 P
nextp puintptr // 暂存的处理器 P
oldp puintptr // 执行系统调用之前的使用线程的处理器 P
id int64
mallocing int32
throwing int32
preemptoff string // if != "", keep curg running on this m
locks int32
dying int32
profilehz int32
spinning bool // m 是否处于自旋状态（处于这个状态的 m 在没有可运行的 g 时，积极寻找可运行 g）
blocked bool // m is blocked on a note
newSigstack bool // minit on C thread called sigaltstack
printlock int8
incgo bool // m is executing a cgo call
freeWait uint32 // if == 0, safe to free g0 and delete m (atomic)
fastrand [2]uint32
needextram bool
traceback uint8
ncgocall uint64 // number of cgo calls in total
ncgo int32 // number of cgo calls currently in progress
cgoCallersUse uint32 // if non-zero, cgoCallers in use temporarily
cgoCallers *cgoCallers // cgo traceback if crashing in cgo call
park note
alllink *m // on allm
schedlink muintptr
mcache *mcache
lockedg guintptr
createstack [32]uintptr // stack that created this thread.
lockedExt uint32 // tracking for external LockOSThread
lockedInt uint32 // tracking for internal lockOSThread
nextwaitm muintptr // next m waiting for lock
waitunlockf func(*g, unsafe.Pointer) bool
waitlock unsafe.Pointer
waittraceev byte
waittraceskip int
startingtrace bool
syscalltick uint32
freelink *m // on sched.freem
// these are here because they are too large to be on the stack
// of low-level NOSPLIT functions.
libcall libcall
libcallpc uintptr // for cpu profiler
libcallsp uintptr
libcallg guintptr
syscall libcall // stores syscall parameters on windows
vdsoSP uintptr // SP for traceback while in VDSO call (0 if not in call)
vdsoPC uintptr // PC for traceback while in VDSO call
// preemptGen counts the number of completed preemption
// signals. This is used to detect when a preemption is
// requested, but fails. Accessed atomically.
preemptGen uint32
dlogPerM
mOS

p.font: // 处理器
type p struct {
id int32
status uint32 // 处理器的状态
link puintptr // 指向可运行 P 链表
schedtick uint32 // 每次调度都会加一
syscalltick uint32 // 每次系统调用都会加一
sysmontick sysmontick // 与 sysmon() 调用相关，last tick observed by sysmon
m muintptr // 指向关联的 m
mcache *mcache
pcache pageCache
raceprocctx uintptr
deferpool [5][]*_defer // pool of available defer structs of different sizes (see panic.go)
deferpoolbuf [5][32]*_defer
// Cache of goroutine ids, amortizes accesses to runtime·sched.goidgen.
goidcache uint64
goidcacheend uint64
// 可运行 goroutne 队列。Accessed without lock.
runqhead uint32 // 队列头
runqtail uint32 // 队列尾
runq [256]guintptr // 队列的底层数组
// runnext, if non-nil, is a runnable G that was ready'd by
// the current G and should be run next instead of what's in
// runq if there's time remaining in the running G's time
// slice. It will inherit the time left in the current time
// slice. If a set of goroutines is locked in a
// communicate-and-wait pattern, this schedules that set as a
// unit and eliminates the (potentially large) scheduling
// latency that otherwise arises from adding the ready'd
// goroutines to the end of the run queue.
runnext guintptr // 线程下一个需要执行的 goroutine
// 空闲 G (status == Gdead) 列表
gFree struct {
gList
n int32
sudogcache []*sudog
sudogbuf [128]*sudog
// Cache of mspan objects from the heap.
mspancache struct {
// We need an explicit length here because this field is used
// in allocation codepaths where write barriers are not allowed,
// and eliminating the write barrier/keeping it eliminated from
// slice updates is tricky, moreso than just managing the length
// ourselves.
len int
buf [128]*mspan
tracebuf traceBufPtr
// traceSweep indicates the sweep events should be traced.
// This is used to defer the sweep start event until a span
// has actually been swept.
traceSweep bool
// traceSwept and traceReclaimed track the number of bytes
// swept and reclaimed by sweeping in the current sweep loop.
traceSwept, traceReclaimed uintptr
palloc persistentAlloc // per-P to avoid mutex

p.span: _ uint32 // Alignment for atomic fields below

p.font: // The when field of the first entry on the timer heap.
// This is updated using atomic functions.
// This is 0 if the timer heap is empty.
timer0When uint64
// Per-P GC state
gcAssistTime int64 // Nanoseconds in assistAlloc
gcFractionalMarkTime int64 // Nanoseconds in fractional mark worker (atomic)
gcBgMarkWorker guintptr // (atomic)
gcMarkWorkerMode gcMarkWorkerMode
// gcMarkWorkerStartTime is the nanotime() at which this mark
// worker started.
gcMarkWorkerStartTime int64
// gcw is this P's GC work buffer cache. The work buffer is
// filled by write barriers, drained by mutator assists, and
// disposed on certain GC state transitions.
gcw gcWork
// wbBuf is this P's GC write barrier buffer.
// TODO: Consider caching this in the running G.
wbBuf wbBuf
runSafePointFn uint32 // 如果值为 1，则在下一个安全点运行 sched.safePointFn
// Lock for timers. We normally access the timers while running
// on this P, but the scheduler can also do it from a different P.
timersLock mutex
// Actions to take at some time. This is used to implement the
// standard library's time package.
// Must hold timersLock to access.
timers []*timer
// Number of timers in P's heap.
// Modified using atomic instructions.
numTimers uint32
// Number of timerModifiedEarlier timers on P's heap.
// This should only be modified while holding timersLock,
// or while the timer status is in a transient state
// such as timerModifying.
adjustTimers uint32
// Number of timerDeleted timers in P's heap.
// Modified using atomic instructions.
deletedTimers uint32
// Race context used while executing timer functions.
timerRaceCtx uintptr
// 设置 preempt 表示，这个 P 应该尽快进入调度（不管上面运行着哪种 G）
preempt bool
pad cpu.CacheLinePad

p.span: const (

p.font: // _Pidle 表示处理器没有运行用户代码或者被调度器使用。
// 一般情况下，处于这种状态的处理器位于空闲 P 列表中，并且对调度器可用
// 运行队列为空
_Pidle = iota
// _Prunning 表示这个 P 被线程 M 占有，并且正在运行用户代码或者被调度器使用
// 只有拥有这个 P 的线程 M 才能将这个 P 的状态从
p.span: _Prunning 更改为其他状态。

p.font: // 线程 M 可能会将这个 P 修改为 _Pidle 状态（当 P 没有更多的任务要执行时），
// _Psyscall 状态（当进行系统调用时），或者 _Pgcstop 状态（因为 GC 停止时）。
// 线程 M 也有可能将这个 P 的所有权直接移交给其他 M（例如，当调度一个被锁的 G 时）
_Prunning
// _Psyscall 表示这个 P 没有在运行用户代码。It has
// affinity to an M in a syscall but is not owned by it and
// may be stolen by another M. This is similar to _Pidle but
// uses lightweight transitions and maintains M affinity.
// Leaving _Psyscall must be done with a CAS, either to steal
// or retake the P. Note that there's an ABA hazard: even if
// an M successfully CASes its original P back to _Prunning
// after a syscall, it must understand the P may have been
// used by another M in the interim.
_Psyscall
// _Pgcstop 表示这个 P 因为 STW 而停止，并且被发起 STW 的线程 M 所持有
// 发起 STW 的线程 M 继续使用它的处理器 P（即使处于
p.span: _Pgcstop 状态）。

p.font: // 从 _Prunning 转变成 _Pgcstop 会导致线程 M 释放它的 P 并且
p.span: park.

p.font: // The P retains its run queue and startTheWorld will restart
// the scheduler on Ps with non-empty run queues.
_Pgcstop
// _Pdead 表示这个 P 已经不再被使用 (GOMAXPROCS shrank)。
// 如果 GOMAXPROCS 增加时，会重新使用 P。 A dead P is mostly
// stripped of its resources, though a few things remain
p.span: (e.g., trace buffers).

p.font: _Pdead
